-- Persian Gulf Stocks: Al-Madina for Finance and Dana Gas Moved
-- B y   Z a h r a   H a n k i r
-- 2012-06-25T11:11:34Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-06-25/persian-gulf-stocks-al-madina-for-finance-and-dana-gas-moved.html
Dubai’s benchmark  DFM General Index (DFMGI) 
retreated 0.3 percent to 1,456.32 at the 2 p.m. close in the
emirate, the lowest level since June 6. The measure is up 7.6
percent this year. Qatar’s  QE Index (DSM)  was little changed.  The following shares were active in the Persian Gulf
region. Stock symbols are in parentheses.  Al-Madina for Finance and Investment Co. SAKC  (ALMADINA KK)
fell 5.3 percent to 45 fils, the lowest since Jan. 9. The
Kuwaiti Islamic investment company said chief executive officer
Mamdouh Al Sherbiny resigned.  Dana Gas PJSC (DANA)   gained 2.7 percent, the first
advance since June 20, to 38 fils. The fuel producer with $1
billion in Islamic bonds maturing in October said it resumed
partial production at its Khor Mor liquefied petroleum gas plant
in the Kurdish region of  Iraq  after a fire.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Zahra Hankir in Dubai at 
